ll this change can be difficult to handle. A Life of Worry unpacks an ethnographic puzzle. What accounts for the simultaneous rise of economic prosperity and anxiety among Ho Chi Minh City's middle class? The social context of anxiety in Vietnam is layered within the development of advanced capitalism, the history of the medical and psychological sciences, and new ways of drawing the line between self and society. At a time when people around the world are turning to the pharmaceutical and wellness industries to soothe their troubled minds, it is worth considering the social and political dynamics that make the promises of these industries so appealing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAnxietyxPolitical aspectszVietnam. 0aAnxietyxSocial aspectszVietnam. 0aMental healthxSocial aspectszVietnam. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520392175zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520392175zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520392175/original  a978-3-11-079134-1 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA